[Briefhoofd: Phaidon Press, London]: Korte inhoud: Zag in het Bowes Museum een werk waarvan hij een afbeelding stuurt (in bijlage); [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'Thanked by telephone. 'F.G. 'P. Breughel fecit 1563' renders the name in the form used by P.B.II or P.B.III. Clearly a carnival picture with eggs, playing cards, kitchenspoons etc. (cf. Vienna Carnival &Lent). Probably 17th century painting, but doubtful whether done by a member of the Brueghel family. The bagpipe player on a 3 cornered chair comparable to the drawing in Dresden, published not convincingly as P.B.I by Tolnay in Miscellanea J.Q. van Regteren Altena 1969. May be connected with some print.'; 1 zw/w foto [Notitie in onbekend handschrift]: Bowes Museum BM 232. Boars masquerading and carousing. Panel 9 1/2" x 12 3/4"
